an therefore be performed\nif velocity disperion data are available out to 10 Mpc radii for nearby\nclusters (less at higher redshifts). For Virgo it appears that there is no such\ncutoff.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 24 May 2006 02:57:51 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 27 Jul 2006 23:30:50 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 16 Aug 2006 03:25:51 GMT"}],"update_date":"2007-05-23"}
